OL,3,CMan jailed for 19 years after
OL,4,C'slashing' adopted mother's throat
OL,6,F"In addition to the physical pain, she
OL,7,Fhas been left heartbroken that Bates
OL,8,Fcould subject her to such a vicious
OL,9,Fattack, despite having adopted him
OL,10,Fwhen his birth mother died.
OL,12,F"Unsurprisingly this incident has had
OL,13,Fa very profound impact on the victim
OL,14,Fso I hope she can draw some comfort
OL,15,Ffrom this sentence.
OL,17,F"Bates is a dangerous and violent man
OL,18,Fand I am pleased he will now spend a
OL,19,Fvery considerable amount of time
OL,20,Fbehind bars."
